Sovereign Heritage Core

Your Secure Personal Database

This is the standalone Sovereign Heritage Core project root. It provides high-grade encryption services and legacy succession protocols as a decoupled microservice.

📂 Directory Structure

/core: Compiled libraries and encryption wrappers.

/vault_backups: Encrypted "Blobs" for disaster recovery.

/config: System-level settings and translation layers.

/logs: Security audits and heartbeat logs.

/templates: HTML interfaces for the Vault Explorer.

🚀 Service Architecture

The core runs as an independent Flask service on Port 5002. It exposes two primary endpoints for data management:

POST /seal: Takes plain text and returns an AES-256-GCM encrypted blob.

POST /open: Takes an encrypted blob and returns the original text (requires Master Key).

🛡️ Security Protocol

Standard: AES-256-GCM (Authenticated Encryption).

Derivation: PBKDF2 with 100,000 iterations.

Philosophy: Zero-Knowledge. The server hosting the database cannot read the contents without the user's volatile Master Password.

